# AgentChattr Control Panel (ACP)

AgentChattr Control Panel (ACP) is a Windows-focused desktop GUI for installing, configuring, and running [`agentchattr`](https://github.com/bcurts/agentchattr).

Its job is to make multi-agent setup and daily operation practical for non-terminal workflows:
- setup and validate dependencies
- manage project workspaces
- configure `config.toml` (including dynamic agents)
- handle LAN/security helpers
- run/stop server and wrappers
- view live logs in one place

## Current Features

- Setup workflow for `agentchattr` clone/pull, `.venv` creation/repair, and optional CLI installs (`codex`, `gemini`)
- Workspace profile management with active workspace selection
- Codex trust + Windows ACL checks/repair helpers for workspace-write compatibility
- Dynamic agent editor for any number of `[agents.*]` entries
- Presets system (built-in + custom) for fast agent creation
- Per-agent advanced config support via "Additional TOML options"
- Server controls (start/stop/open chat)
- Per-agent wrapper controls generated from current config
- LAN host + origin patch workflow
- Consolidated logs for setup/run diagnostics

## Caveats

- Live status updates and agent "stop" mechanisms are experimental and may not function correctly. Stopping agents is best done by closing their respective terminal windows instead of using "Stop". 

## Requirements

- Python 3.11+
- Windows 10/11 recommended
- Git (for cloning/updating `agentchattr`)
- Node.js + npm (only needed if ACP installs CLI agents for you)

## Install and Run

### Option A (recommended)

```bat
run_acp.bat
```

### Option B (manual)

```bat
cd /d <this-folder>
python -m venv .venv
.venv\Scripts\activate.bat
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
python -m acp
```

